# planckConstant

- _planckConstant(n)_

Answer _n_ times the Planck constant,
a fundamental physical constant ordinarily written as _h_,
given in joules per hertz (_J/Hz_).

```
>>> 1.planckConstant
6.62607015 * (10 ^ -34)
```

Decimal expansion,
OEIS [A003676](https://oeis.org/A003676):

```
>>> 1.planckConstant
>>> .realDigits(10, 10)
[[0 6 6 2 6 0 7 0 1 5], -32]
```

The reduced Planck constant,
denoted ℏ:

```
>>> 1.planckConstant / 2.pi
1.054571E-34
```

* * *

See also: e, fineStructureConstant, pi

